Regression example

This is a simple bivariate regression example. Two plus two equals 4.

2+2

Tidy some data

Here we tidy the data.

my_data <- spanish%>%
  select(., x = X14461gll, y = X14473gll)%>%
  filter(., y < 0.06, x < 0.075)

my_data%>%
  ggplot(., aes(x = x, y = y))+
    geom_point() +
    geom_smooth(method= 'lm')

Model

here we fit a model.

my_fit <- lm(y~x, data = my_data)
summary(my_fit)

my_data <- spanish%>%
  select(., x = X14474gll, y = X14467gll) %>%
  filter(., y < 0.05, x < 0.025)

my_data%>%
  ggplot(., aes(x = x, y = y)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_smooth(method= 'lm')

my_summary <- lm(y~x, data = my_data)
summary(my_summary)
